  <a href="#0" id="0">
   In this paper we apply recursive neural networks to political ideology detection, a problem where previous work relies heavily on bag-of-words models and hand-designed lexica.
  </a>
  <a href="#1" id="1">
   We show that our approach detects bias more accurately than existing methods on two different datasets.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   In addition, we describe an approach to crowdsourcing ideological bias annotations.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   We use this approach to create a new dataset from the ibc , which is labeled at both the sentence and phrase level.
  </a>
